# SkyWeb Change Log

Detailed implementation notes live here so `README.md` can stay focused on current status, setup, and architecture.

## Current Feature Baseline

### Phase 8.8 — Alert Rule UX Polish

Completed alert-system cockpit polish:

- Alert rule search, filter, and sort controls.
- Inline edit mode for existing alert rules.
- Clone rule action, staged inactive by default.
- Safer remove confirmation.
- Better client-side validation for missing target/metric/threshold inputs.
- Alert detail edit handoff back to `/macro/alerts?edit=:alertKey`.

### Phase 8 — Macro Alerts Completed Scope

- 8.1: Alert rules foundation, create rules, conditions, manual evaluation.
- 8.2: Alert detail page and evaluation history.
- 8.3: Scheduled alert evaluation visibility from SkyServer Worker.
- 8.4: Triggered notification queue with acknowledge/dismiss lifecycle.
- 8.5: Navbar Signals pill, dashboard alert card, Macro Overview signal strip, lifecycle wording, severity styling.
- 8.6: Alert preferences and delivery-prep contract.
- 8.7: Dedicated Signal Center.
- 8.8: Alert-rule UX polish.

## .NET Transition Lane

### DN-0 — Preserve Pre-.NET Baseline

- Captured existing SkyWeb Analytics feature baseline before introducing the parallel ASP.NET Core lane.
- Added baseline documentation for public macro routes, authenticated routes, alert routes, and Phase 8.8 behavior.

### DN-1 — Create Parallel .NET App Structure

- Added `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.DotNet.sln`.
- Added `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Api` as the ASP.NET Core API project.
- Added `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Client` as a copied React/Vite client for migration testing.
- Kept existing `apps/web` untouched as the production baseline.

### DN-2 — Configure API, CORS, Health, DB Connection

- Added `/_health` endpoint.
- Added `/_db/health` endpoint.
- Added Swagger/OpenAPI support.
- Added CORS support for the existing app and the .NET-lane client.
- Added PostgreSQL connection factory using the existing `skyserver_dev` database.
- Added guidance for .NET user secrets so local DB passwords are not committed.

### DN-3 — Wire SkyWeb.Client to SkyWeb.Api

- Added `VITE_SKYWEB_API_BASE_URL` support for the .NET-lane client.
- Added temporary proxy bridge through `SkyWeb.Api`.
- Proxied `/api/auth/*`, `/api/skyweb/*`, and `/api/public/macro/*` during early migration.
- Moved the .NET-lane React client to port `5175` so it can run beside the existing app on `5174`.

### DN-4 — Public Macro REST Endpoints in C#

- Replaced `/api/public/macro/*` proxy fallback with native ASP.NET Core/C# endpoints.
- Added native routes for macro summary, views, columns, latest rows, view rows, indicators, indicator detail, and indicator series.
- Left `/api/auth/*` and `/api/skyweb/*` on proxy fallback pending later DN phases.

### DN-5 — Authentication in C#

- Added native ASP.NET Core/C# authentication endpoints:
  - `POST /api/auth/login`
  - `POST /api/auth/logout`
  - `POST /api/auth/change-password`
  - `GET /api/auth/me`
  - `GET /api/auth/permissions`
- Added native bearer-token session validation middleware.
- Mirrored the existing opaque bearer-token model using raw session tokens and SHA-256 token hashes in `auth.sessions.session_token_hash`.
- Mirrored app-scoped auth using `core.applications`, `auth.user_applications`, and `auth.vw_user_permissions`.
- Mirrored login event and audit event writes.
- Kept `/api/skyweb/*` on proxy fallback for DN-6 through DN-8.
